Pineapple Spice Pulled Pork Sliders

One of the easiest things to make for a crowd. 

Recipe & what you’ll need. 
 
Set your @traegergrills 165’F

1 - Pork butt (8-10lbs) trimmed up with your @montanaknifecompany knife
  Mustard

Rub:
(I make lots)
1/2 cup @traegergrills Anything Rub
1/2 cup  @traegergrills Pork n Poultry Rub
1/2 cup Demers Sugar
1/8 cup Granulated Garlic Powder
1/8 cup Chili Flakes
2 Tbsp Onion Powder 
2 Tsp Chipotle Powder
Jalapeños
Pineapple Juice

-Pat dry Pork Butt, rub mustard to coat,
Mix rub and cover pork butt. 
Place your butt on your @traegergrills 
And let smoke for 5 hours. 

Turn @traegergrills up to 225’F
Take butt off @traegergrills place in a foil or roaster pan. Pour 3-4 cups of pineapple juice over it and fill pan 1/2 way with juice. 
Sprinkle on more rub mix. Slice jalapeños and place all over. 
You can add more pepper flakes and chipotle if you want more of a kick. Cover with foil. 
Cook for another  5 hours covered. 

This will shred and fall apart. Add some of the liquid if desired. I do a bit to get the consistency I like. 
I finished it with some @traegergrills 
Show me the Honey Sauce 

Get out some sweet rolls, pickles and some Granny Smith slaw and your all set. 
Enjoy!!!

Antelope Island Adventure on Easter weekend!

What a beautiful day to explore! 
Hiking, picnic, laughing, Antelope, Burrowing Owls, bunnies, Bison, BIG Bison, Bison Calves, Salt Lake, song birds, Chukar and coyotes and being so thankful for this day. 
As we were leaving we saw 2 coyotes on a bison calf kill. 
Yes it’s a part of the circle of life, but it never gets easier to witness. Something so innocent and pure had to suffer and die. 

It made me reflect even more about this weekend, about how Jesus made the ultimate sacrifice for us, so that we may have eternal life. That he gave it all at the Cross for us. 

Easter isn’t about bunnies, Chocolate, new church dresses, big dinners or sporting events, it’s all about my Lord and Savior Jesus!! 
“From the cross to the grave, from the grave to the sky, Lord I lift your name on high!” Amen thank you Jesus for saving my life! 
#amen #easter #jesus #jesusislord #thecross #truelove #glory #saviour #family #grace #love

@traegergrills Flatrock makes life so easy!!

Sesame Fried Rice & Ginger Pork Tenderloin with Udon Noodle Stir fry

Ingredients 
2-Pork Tenderloin sliced 
Marinate-
1/2 cup Low Sodium Soy Sauce
1-2 cup Brown Sugar
1/4 cup water
2 tsp minced ginger
1 tsp minced garlic
Marinate in fridge over night or for at least 6 hours. 

Fried Rice
4 cups cooked rice
1 cup frozen peas and/or carrots
Traeger Anything rub to taste 
Sesame oil light drizzle
1/4 cup Low Sodium Soy sauce or a little more to taste

4cups Udon noodles (I put them in a pot and bring them to a boil first/drain well- makes them softer)

Sesame oil 
Olive oil
Green Onions
Sesame seeds
Mushrooms
Carrots

Get your @traegergrills Flatrock heated up
You have 3 areas you can set temp at. 
Set to medium, then you can adjust your temp from there. 
Pour meat on and stir fry until cooked. Add thinly cut carrots if desired. Add udon noodles. A little soy sauce, cook for 5 min. Then add cleaned mushrooms. Cook for 5 min. 

On the other side of the grill add some olive oil, drop on cooked rice. Warm that up and add some anything spice.
In the middle add oil, scramble up your eggs. Season. Mix with rice, add veggies, a teaspoon sesame oil. Add 1/4 cup soy sauce(this is a to taste ) Keep flipping it to get it nice and fried and crispy. 
Once cooked place in serving dishes ant top with sesame seeds and green onions!!
Enjoy!!!

Smoked Garlic Butter Brisket
Brisket with a Twist

🏹Start up your @traegergrills  and set temp to 185’ 
🏹Trim up brisket
🏹Give it a good mustard massage 
🏹Mix up your favorite seasoning mix 
🏹Rub it all over and wrap it up
🏹Smoke on your @traegergrills for about 7 hours
🏹Then take it off and slather it with Smoked Garlic Butter
🏹Wrap it up. Place on grill and @meatermade probe it
🏹Smoke for 4 hours at 185
🏹Turn up temp to 225’ , set probe for 203’ and let it roll
🏹Once it hits 203’ , remove from grill and place in your @yeti cooler to rest, for about an hour. 
🏹Slice it up and serve with more Garlic Butter. 

🏹ENJOY!!

#traeger #traegergameday #traegergrills #traegernation #brisket #rivetco #smokeit #favorite #delicious #celebrate #foodporn #grillit #epic #picoftheday

My Spice Rub
1/2-1cup Brown sugar
1/4 cup Traeger Rub
3Tbsp Granulated Garlic Powder 
3Tbsp Granulated Onion Powder 
2Tbsp Himalayan or Celtic Salt
2Tbsp Chipotle Powder 
2-3 tsp Cayenne Pepper
1/8 cup Smoked Paprika 

***************************
My Smoked Garlic butter

In a pot or pan place in garlic, EVOO, butter and salt. 

1cup peeled garlic
1/2cup EVOO
1/2cup butter
1tsp Himalayan or Celtic salt 

Smoke at 225’ until garlic is tender and sweet. 
(I smoke mine low and slow to get as much smoke and get the garlic caramelized and sweet)
When garlic is soft, I place into my mini food processor and carefully pulse it. Until creamy. (If it get to thick, microwave it)

Jenns Smoked Thanksgiving Organic Ham🍖

Epic, clean, delicious Ham

Here’s the recipe. 

I- 10-15lb fresh farm raised pork ham (hind quarter)

Brine:in a large sauce pan combine, bring to a boil for 5 minutes let cool, add 2 cups cold water

4 cups water
2 cups dark brown sugar
1 cup dark molasses
2 cups Pink Himalayan Salt
Place 
2 tbsp pickling spice
2tbsp dried garlic
2 tbsp dried onion 
1 tbsp fennel
1 tbsp pepper flakes
In cheesecloth square and tie
Place ham in a food safe container, so it will just fit with enough room for liquids
Pro tip** if your ham is floating, put 1 or 2 dinner plates in a large ziplock for weight on top of ham to keep it submerged 
Then top up liquids. 
I brined Ham for 5 days, flip it everyday. 

After brining is done turn on your @traegergrills and set it to 165. 
I’m using the new @meatermade + just released. Place MEATER probe in thickest meat close to bone. 
I eat my alarm for 150. smoked for 12 hours)
Spritzing every hour while I was up. 
Then I remove it from grill place it in a roasting pan, 
add 1 cup of dark brown  sugar,
1 can Dr Pepper
1 can root beer 
Cover pan with foil. 
Turn Traeger up to 250. Place on grill. Set alarm on your @meatermade for 225. 
When your alarm goes off take your ham out and let it rest for 15 minutes. 
Enjoy with all you favorite sides!!

Leftover ham makes great soups and sandwiches!!

This was a farm raised hog, that I skinned, butchered down and prepared. Support local farmers. 

Stay tuned for sausage and pepperoni making. Rendering lard and making soap!!
